  1.  Personal contact information belonging to members of the public is exempt from disclosure because it would constitute an unwarranted invasion of personal privacy.  Therefore, the public interest served by redacting private personal contact information outweighs any public interest served by disclosure pursuant to Government Code section 7922.000.


  1.  Non-public contact information for high-ranking UC staff are exempt because the disclosure would negate existing safeguards that protect staff from voluminous emails and phishing attempts, and undermine the secure scheduling and timely and effective, day-to-day communications of staff. Therefore, the public interest served by redacting non-public contact information clearly outweighs any public interest served by disclosure, pursuant to Government Code section 7922.000.

Sincerely,

Dan Scannell
Office of General Counsel
University of California
